1H Pass 2D Pass 2H Pass 3H Pass 4C Pass 4D Pass 4NT Pass 5H Pass 6H Pass Pass Pass
{How do you respond with this nice hand?
With 16+ points and 3 \Hs, you will insist on a \H game at a minimum. But there is no need to start making jump bids, so start with a simple 2\D bid.  This is natural and game forcing.  South rebids 2\H to show a 6-card suit.  What do you rebid now?
Now you say 3\H to set the trump suit, and show slam interest.  At this point South also shows slam interest, making a control-showing bid of 4\C. Do you cooperate? 
Yes, you have an easy, 4\D bid, showing the \DA.
South has heard enough. He bids 4NT.  What do you respond, playing standard Blackwood?

When partner hears about your two aces, he bids the slam.}

